    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nThis assertion fails occasionally while editing code:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/f67517bba30b6233bea85e1f6a8505171142d4ca/src/nvim/msgpack_rpc/unpacker.c#L467\r\n\r\nI can force it to fail by scrolling very quickly.\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n`repro.lua`:\r\n```lua\r\nfunction Repro()\r\n  vim.defer_fn(function()\r\n    local move_direction = math.random(2)\r\n    if move_direction == 1 then\r\n      for i=1,10 do\r\n        vim.api.nvim_feedkeys(\"5k\", \"n\", false)\r\n      end\r\n    else\r\n      for i=1,10 do\r\n        vim.api.nvim_feedkeys(\"5j\", \"n\", false)\r\n      end\r\n    end\r\n    Repro()\r\n  end, 0.05)\r\nend\r\n```\r\n\r\n```sh\r\nnvim --noplugin --clean -u repro.lua src/nvim/msgpack_rpc/unpacker.c\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt should crash within 30 seconds. If you get bored you can drag the corner of the terminal around while spamming `<C-c>` to try and mess with it more.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nNo crash.\r\n\r\n### Additional Info\r\n\r\nI added some additional asserts to try and see what's going on:\r\n```diff\r\ndiff --git a/src/nvim/msgpack_rpc/unpacker.c b/src/nvim/msgpack_rpc/unpacker.c\r\nindex 3aa1ba122..6afb6e4a7 100644\r\n--- a/src/nvim/msgpack_rpc/unpacker.c\r\n+++ b/src/nvim/msgpack_rpc/unpacker.c\r\n@@ -458,13 +458,18 @@ bool unpacker_parse_redraw(Unpacker *p)\r\n     p->read_size = size;\r\n     p->state = 15;\r\n \r\n+    assert(tok.length >= 0);\r\n     if ((int)tok.length == 0) {\r\n       return true;\r\n     }\r\n     FALLTHROUGH;\r\n \r\n   case 15:\r\n+    assert(g->ncells > 0);\r\n+    int prev = -1;\r\n     while (true) {\r\n+      assert(g->icell <= prev + 1);\r\n+      prev = g->icell;\r\n       assert(g->icell < g->ncells);\r\n \r\n       NEXT_TYPE(tok, MPACK_TOKEN_ARRAY);\r\n```\r\n\r\nStrangely the one that's failing is actually the `assert(g->icell <= prev + 1)`. That seems really odd, unless `p` is not thread local? I'll put it in a mutex and see what happens\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nbe10d65bf (0.10 nightly)\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nno\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nMacOS 13.4.1\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nkitty 0.28.1\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-kitty\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nbuild from repo",
